# UI Component Guidelines

- **Grid Layout Patterns**
  - **Consistent Grid Structure**
    - Use 3-column grid for item collections: `grid-cols-3`
    - Use 2-column grid for larger items or when more detail is needed: `grid-cols-2`
    - Apply consistent gap: `gap-2` for compact layouts
    ```jsx
    // ✅ DO: Use consistent grid patterns
    <div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-2">
      {items.map(item => (/* Item content */))}
    </div>
    
    // ❌ DON'T: Use inconsistent grid columns
    <div className="grid grid-cols-4 gap-1">
      {items.map(item => (/* Item content */))}
    </div>
    ```

- **Item Card Styling**
  - **Consistent Height**
    - Use fixed heights for grid items: `h-16` for compact cards
    - Center content vertically and horizontally: `flex items-center justify-center`
  - **Selection Indicators**
    - Use subtle blue highlighting for selected items: `ring-1 ring-blue-500 border-blue-300 bg-blue-50`
    - Use gray borders for non-selected items: `border-gray-200 hover:border-gray-300`
    ```jsx
    // ✅ DO: Use consistent selection styling
    <div 
      className={`
        cursor-pointer rounded p-1.5 flex flex-col items-center justify-center border h-16 
        ${isSelected ? 'ring-1 ring-blue-500 border-blue-300 bg-blue-50' : 'border-gray-200 hover:border-gray-300'}
      `}
    >
      {/* Content */}
    </div>
    ```

- **Typography Scale**
  - **Consistent Text Sizes**
    - Use `text-[10px]` for card labels and small UI text
    - Use `text-xs` (12px) for section headers
    - Use `font-medium` instead of `font-bold` for better readability at small sizes
    ```jsx
    // ✅ DO: Follow the typography scale
    <h3 className="text-xs font-medium mb-1">Section Title</h3>
    <span className="text-[10px] font-medium">Item Label</span>
    
    // ❌ DON'T: Use inconsistent text sizes
    <h3 className="text-sm font-bold">Section Title</h3>
    <span className="text-xs font-bold">Item Label</span>
    ```

- **Spacing and Layout**
  - **Compact Spacing**
    - Use `mb-1` or `mt-0.5` for vertical spacing between elements
    - Use `p-1.5` for card padding
    - Use `pt-1` for section top padding
    ```jsx
    // ✅ DO: Use compact, consistent spacing
    <div className="pt-1">
      <h3 className="text-xs font-medium mb-2">Section Title</h3>
      <div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-2 mb-3">
        {/* Items */}
      </div>
    </div>
    ```

- **Interactive Elements**
  - **Buttons and Controls**
    - Use `px-2 py-0.5` padding for small buttons
    - Use `text-[10px]` for button text
    - Use `border-gray-200` for default borders
    - Use `border-blue-500 bg-blue-50` for active/selected state
    ```jsx
    // ✅ DO: Use consistent button styling
    <button 
      className={`px-2 py-0.5 text-[10px] border rounded hover:bg-gray-50 
        ${isActive ? 'border-blue-500 bg-blue-50' : 'border-gray-200'}`}
    >
      Button Text
    </button>
    ```

- **Tab Component Styling**
  - **Tab Navigation**
    - Use `px-3 py-1.5 text-xs` for tab buttons
    - Use `border-b-2 border-blue-500 text-blue-600` for active tab
    - Use `text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-700` for inactive tabs
    ```jsx
    // ✅ DO: Follow tab styling pattern
    <button
      className={`px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium 
        ${isActive ? 'border-b-2 border-blue-500 text-blue-600' : 'text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-700'}`}
    >
      Tab Name
    </button>
    ```

- **Panel Containers**
  - **Scrollable Containers**
    - Use `overflow-y-auto` for scrollable content
    - Use `flex-1` to allow container to fill available space
    ```jsx
    <div className="p-2 overflow-y-auto flex-1">
      {/* Scrollable content */}
    </div>
    ```

